Stateless:
kubectl create deployment kubernetes-bootcamp --image=gcr.io/google-samples/kubernetes-bootcamp:v1

Statefull:
# MySQL Steps
Download YAML files: mysql-pv and mysql-deploy
*validate IP address in mysql-deploy.yaml file, change it to match your IP address node.

sudo kubectl apply -f mysql-pv.yaml
sudo kubectl apply -f mysql-deploy.yaml

sudo kubectl get pods -n mysql
sudo kubectl get svc -n mysql
sudo kubectl get pv -n mysql
sudo kubectl get pvc -n mysql

Access to mysql engine:
sudo kubectl run -it --rm --image=mysql:9 --restart=Never mysql-client -- mysql -h mysql -ppassword
*Validate mysql hostname. In the YAML file i used my node ip address: 192.168.1.122 (change it).

